      • setItemLater

        public static void setItemLater(InventoryGui gui,
                                int slot,
                                org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item)
        Stores the ItemStack at the given index of a GUI's inventory. The inventory is only updated the next time the Bukkit Scheduler runs (i.e. next server tick).
        Parameters:
        gui - The GUI to update
        slot - The slot where to put the ItemStack
        item - The ItemStack to set

      • makeItem

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack makeItem(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack itemStack,
                                                      String title,
                                                      List<String> loreLines)
        One-liner to update an ItemStack's ItemMeta.

        If the stack is a map, it's attributes will be hidden.

        Parameters:
        itemStack - The original ItemStack. This stack will be directly modified.
        title - The stack's title.
        loreLines - A list containing the stack's lines.
        Returns:
        The same ItemStack, but with an updated ItemMeta.
